abstract: The state would become the second in the nation, behind Michigan, to outlaw sale of the fruity flavors popular with children and teenagers.
snippet: The state would become the second in the nation, behind Michigan, to outlaw sale of the fruity flavors popular with children and teenagers.
lead_paragraph: Amid a surge of vaping-related illnesses and deaths, Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo of New York announced on Sunday that he would pursue emergency regulations this week to quickly ban the sale of flavored e-cigarettes.

lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Robert A. Iger, Disney’s chief executive and chairman, has resigned from the board of Apple, whose growing Hollywood operation would have made it harder for him to fully engage as one of its directors.

abstract: The economy seems to be cooling off. Whether it starts to shrink is the question.
snippet: The economy seems to be cooling off. Whether it starts to shrink is the question.
lead_paragraph: The United States is on recession watch as market signals flash red. Manufacturing is straining under President Trump’s trade war, business investment is slowing and consumer confidence is showing cracks.

headline_print_headline: A Cooling Economy, Sure. A Recession? Complicated.

abstract: In a new Travel column, Sarah Firshein aims to help travelers resolve their thorniest and most upsetting travel disasters. This week, she investigates a nonexistent hotel, booked on Expedia.
snippet: In a new Travel column, Sarah Firshein aims to help travelers resolve their thorniest and most upsetting travel disasters. This week, she investigates a nonexistent hotel, booked on Expedia.
lead_paragraph: What a way to end the year; when people set off on New Year’s adventures, this isn’t exactly what they have in mind. But you did everything right: You handled the immediate need first and dealt with the larger customer-service complaint afterward. If your children didn’t think of you as a superhero before, they certainly do now.

abstract: The heads of 145 companies sent a letter to Senate leaders calling for an expansion of background checks to firearms sales and stronger gun laws.
snippet: The heads of 145 companies sent a letter to Senate leaders calling for an expansion of background checks to firearms sales and stronger gun laws.
lead_paragraph: Good Thursday morning. I’m in Washington this afternoon for the DealBook D.C. Summit, where other NYT journalists and I will talk with business and policy leaders about trade, antitrust and more. You can watch my interview with Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin at 5 p.m. Eastern here. (Was this email forwarded to you? Sign up here.)
